# Pow (real exponentiation) — intended semantics (reference)
#
# - x > 0, y in R: x^y = exp(y * ln(x)) (standard real power).
# - x != 0, y in Z: algebraic integer power; x^0 = 1 for x != 0.
# - x = 0, y > 0: often 0^y = 0 (limit-consistent with x -> 0+).
# - x = 0, y <= 0: undefined in this convention (includes 0^0 — not allowed).
# - x < 0 with non-integer y: not a single-valued real power in general; use extra
#   hypotheses (e.g. integer or restricted rational exponents) if needed.
#
# Do not treat "y in R_pos and x in R" as a full domain: e.g. (-2)^(1/2) is not real.

7^(1/2) = 7^(1/2)
